    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    • Network Chick
      5.0 out of 5 stars Best Frugal Smart Watch for Android
      Reviewed in the United States on March 24, 2024
      Verified Purchase
      I am beyond satisfied with this watch! I have had multiple budget watches and none of them hit all the marks. Note that I don't need a speaker or phone call capability and am an amateur for fitness. Here are my hits:

      - There are notifications for all my communication apps including SLACK and Discord. Note that it took a reload of the watch and the phone for all apps to show up in the notifications selection list.
      - It controls Audible, not just music.
      - The current weather is synced to the hour and there is a forecast tile as well.
      - The bonus features of taking photos and finding the phone actually work ;)
      - You can double click the power button to set quick access for an app and this is perfect for media controls for Audible and music when you need a quick pause.
      - It auto starts my workout tracking.
      - It is a small form factor and very light to wear, but the screen is large enough to read messages clearly with multiple lines of text. I can't stand oversized watches, and being 6'1" and fluffy, size is not an issue :p
      - I really like the alarm control on the watch itself. You can set an alarm for the watch, the phone, or both.
      - I like the calendar visibilty. I can easily scroll through my daily agenda without having to pull out my phone.
      - No issues with the international version. It changed from Spanish to English during sync/upgrade and everything has been great.
      - So far the battery is amazing. I fully charged it at 10pm last night, have used it off and on all day, and at 9pm tonight it is still at 92%. This is with monitoring every 10 mins and touch to wake screen.
      - The watch is controlled by the Galaxy Wearables app which is much more functional than other interfaces like F Fit or AnyLoop.
      - Outstanding price compared to an Apple equivalent or a even a standard FitBit or Galaxy watch.

      Meh or misses:
      - The watch faces are not super exciting. I would love more modern and dynamic options or more control over customization. I love using my own photo, but then I can't track time, steps, day/month/date, and battery life at the same time.

      Overall, this is a hands down yes recommendation!
